><item><title><![CDATA['We will not leave': Netanyahu visits Israeli troops in 'occupied' southern Lebanon]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132103966.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/we-will-not-leave-netanyahu-visits-israeli-troops-in-occupied-southern-lebanon/articleshow/132103966.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/we-will-not-leave-netanyahu-visits-israeli-troops-in-occupied-southern-lebanon/articleshow/132103966.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T07:44:37+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132104104,imgsize-33942.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA["Charlie was shot in the chest": Candace Owens ignites another online controversy with Charlie Kirk conspiracy narrative]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132103429.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Candace Owens is facing fresh online backlash after critics accused her of fueling conspiracy theories surrounding Charlie Kirk's death. A viral post claimed Owens misrepresented a witness's initial confusion over where Kirk was shot, using it to support broader allegations. The debate quickly spread across social media, with users criticizing Owens, calling for legal action, and expressing concern that the witness and her family have become targets of online harassment amid the growing controversy.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/charlie-was-shot-in-the-chest-candace-owens-ignites-another-online-controversy-with-charlie-kirk-conspiracy-narrative/articleshow/132103429.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/charlie-was-shot-in-the-chest-candace-owens-ignites-another-online-controversy-with-charlie-kirk-conspiracy-narrative/articleshow/132103429.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T05:38:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132103429,imgsize-97869.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Microphone theory’: Candace Owens revives controversial claim in Charlie Kirk assassination case]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132103484.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Charlie Kirk was killed during a TPUSA event in Utah in September 2025, and prosecutors accuse Tyler James Robinson of carrying out a politically motivated assassination. While investigators say forensic evidence strongly supports the lone-gunman case, Candace Owens has continued raising doubts and promoting the “exploding microphone” theory. Her claims have fueled debate online as Robinson’s high-profile case heads toward trial.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/microphone-theory-candace-owens-revives-controversial-claim-in-charlie-kirk-assassination-case/articleshow/132103484.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/microphone-theory-candace-owens-revives-controversial-claim-in-charlie-kirk-assassination-case/articleshow/132103484.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T05:25:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132103477,imgsize-2032559.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Who is Katalina Cartmel? Meet Jack Doherty’s girlfriend after explosive Ring camera footage goes viral]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132103381.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A Ring camera video shared by TMZ shows YouTuber Jack Doherty and girlfriend Katalina Cartmel involved in a heated argument. Cartmel appears to throw a water bottle at Doherty before leaving the room. The clip has sparked strong reactions online. Cartmel is a social media influencer with a large TikTok following, while Doherty remains one of YouTube’s most controversial creators.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/who-is-katalina-cartmel-meet-jack-dohertys-girlfriend-after-explosive-ring-camera-footage-goes-viral/articleshow/132103381.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/who-is-katalina-cartmel-meet-jack-dohertys-girlfriend-after-explosive-ring-camera-footage-goes-viral/articleshow/132103381.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T04:37:58+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132103376,imgsize-735571.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[ExtraEmily banned on Twitch after a near crash changes her latest livestream]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132098973.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[ExtraEmily has been banned from Twitch after a June 28 IRL stream showed her nearly crashing while reading chat during a drive. The incident revived concerns about distracted driving and followed previous controversies, including a viewbotting dispute and an earlier driving-related suspension. The latest ban has again sparked debate over safety rules for livestreamers and the responsibility creators have while broadcasting in public.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/extraemily-banned-on-twitch-after-a-near-crash-changes-her-latest-livestream/articleshow/132098973.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/extraemily-banned-on-twitch-after-a-near-crash-changes-her-latest-livestream/articleshow/132098973.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-30T23:17:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132098939,imgsize-90671.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Don’t broadcast Sheikh Hasina speeches: Bangladesh warns its media outlets]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132103292.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/dont-broadcast-sheikh-hasina-speeches-bangladesh-warns-its-media-outlets/articleshow/132103292.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/dont-broadcast-sheikh-hasina-speeches-bangladesh-warns-its-media-outlets/articleshow/132103292.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T04:09:20+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Ahsan Tasnim</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132103291,imgsize-105904.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Ready for war': Iran draws red line for US, says no final talks until MoU terms are met]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132101599.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Iran's Parliament Speaker has issued a stark warning of war if the US fails to adhere to a memorandum of understanding, emphasizing that negotiations will halt until Washington fulfills its commitments. Tehran views recent Persian Gulf incidents as violations, vowing a strong reaction. Discussions are currently focused on implementing the MoU, including the lifting of a naval blockade and the release of frozen assets, with technical talks planned in Doha.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/ready-for-war-iran-draws-red-line-for-us-says-no-final-talks-until-mou-terms-are-met/articleshow/132101599.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/ready-for-war-iran-draws-red-line-for-us-says-no-final-talks-until-mou-terms-are-met/articleshow/132101599.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T03:31:48+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132101616,imgsize-64449.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why Valkyrae believes Nina Lin should never return to Twitch after recent controversies]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132101364.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Popular YouTuber Valkyrae has voiced strong disapproval over streamer Nina Lin's return to Twitch, citing a pattern of serious controversies. Valkyrae highlighted past allegations involving creators DisguisedToast and Said, alongside Nina's recent arrest in New York for disorderly conduct. She argued these repeated incidents warrant a permanent ban, not a short suspension, questioning Twitch's consistency in enforcing its rules for creators facing multiple serious accusations.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/why-valkyrae-believes-nina-lin-should-never-return-to-twitch-after-recent-controversies/articleshow/132101364.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/why-valkyrae-believes-nina-lin-should-never-return-to-twitch-after-recent-controversies/articleshow/132101364.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T02:23:38+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132101363,imgsize-780222.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[xQc survives scary Lamborghini scare after losing control during live track session]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132101326.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Popular streamer xQc narrowly avoided a serious crash while live-streaming from a Canadian racetrack. His high-performance Lamborghini Huracán Tecnica slid dangerously close to a trackside structure after hitting a curb.  Thanks to xQc's quick reflexes and the instructor's intervention, the supercar was brought back under control, preventing a potential accident. The incident, captured on camera, highlighted the thrilling yet perilous nature of track driving.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/xqc-survives-scary-lamborghini-scare-after-losing-control-during-live-track-session/articleshow/132101326.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/xqc-survives-scary-lamborghini-scare-after-losing-control-during-live-track-session/articleshow/132101326.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T01:54:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132101324,imgsize-568192.cms"/></item></channel></rss>